              <tr> 
                <td height="622" valign="top" colspan="2" bgcolor="#004142">&nbsp;<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">No Escape - The Power Within..........</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Rating</Font></TD><TD><IMG SRC="images/a4.gif" BORDER=0><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=1739"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=1739"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=4361">Bryan "DMX" Prittie</A></FONT></TD></TR><!-- 4361 --><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This article takes a look at a BEASTLY card that now can annihilate the Light Side.....</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Article</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I think I almost spit out my drink when I read the card &#146;No Escape&#146;.  I was in such awe that I immediately dreamed of my old Hunt Down and Destroy the Jedi Dueler coming back (no, it&#146;s not posted on my page).  You see, I have been a big fan of Hunt Down, well, since it&#146;s been released.  I have taken Hunt Down to more than half of my local tournys and not to mention GenCon 99&#146;.  But before I go any further, allow me to introduce the card.<br>
<br>
No Escape [UNIQUE - DESTINY 4 - EFFECT]<br>
Deploy on table.  You may immediately take top card of lost pile into hand.  Effects, Epic Events, and Objectives are immune to Honor of the Jedi.  At each opponent&#146;s &lt;&gt; site, your characters and vehicles deploy -3 and your force generation is +1.  (Immune to Alter.)<br>
<br>
So let&#146;s see, the following decks are no longer in existance when this card is released:<br>
<br>
Throne Room - so long force choke.  You activate 2 at the farm and the swamp if they get both nudjs out first turn. And if they don&#146;t, good old Vader comes down for 3 force (5 if Lord) and starts taking over.  Your walkers deploy for 3 force which means you will completely dominate Yavin 4 and give them no choice, but to come to you.<br>
<br>
Operatives - Yes, they are already dead, but now it&#146;s official, Operatives are cooked like Sushi.	Deploy -3 characters and walkers, and with Leave them To Me out, FW+45 (estimation, but it is no doubt they&#146;ll lose).<br>
<br>
Endor Uprising - No longer will you see this, it will get ugly.  Since you don&#146;t go first, there is a possibility Lord Vader will come to the Farm for 3 force.  Wow....cuz they activate 4 force just from your sites (6 unless you got Strike Planning out).  The quick activation the DS gets from your sites is just not good.<br>
<br>
I&#146;m sure there is more....but those were just some of the BIGGER DECKS THAT ARE NO DONE.<br>
<br>
The effect &#146;No Escape&#146; helps the following DS decks:<br>
<br>
Court - Now you don&#146;t have to occupy 3 battlegrounds to make them lose 1 a turn if they don&#146;t come to you.  Make them lose force right away.	Rancor = GOOOOOD.<br>
<br>
Hunt Down - I think everyone had Hunt Down in mind when they read this card.  You flip and they only lose to Visage again.  I think every new age Hunt Down deck will start with this card.  Dueling will be popular again cuz you won&#146;t need m@#$%ive amounts of characters again to occupy 3 battlegrounds so you don&#146;t lose to Visage.  Then they lose the maximum amount of force when you win a duel.<br>
<br>
Bring Him Before Me - When you duel Luke and win, opponent loses 3 force.  With Honor out, they only lose 1 unless you occupy 3, this can be a pain and drag on the game much longer.  Well, that is over now with this card.<br>
<br>
There might be more, but these are the HUGE decks this card will help.<br>
<br>
Here are some cards &#146;No Escape&#146; will help:<br>
<br>
First Strike - Opponent will always lose 1 now.<br>
There is No Try - Lose 2 to SAC every-time.<br>
Search and Destroy - Now Hidden Base will be cut thru like a knife thru budda (butter).<br>
Security Precautions - Lose 9 force @#$%!  No, not 7, 9!  (If they got 6 systems on table)<br>
<br>
I&#146;m sure there&#146;s more, but my brain is not very well capacitated.<br>
<br>
I think Decipher is now trying to turn Honor of the Jedi into the LS counterpart of Come Here You Big Coward!.	That&#146;s the way it should&#146;ve been all along.<br>
<br>
Bryan &#146;DMX&#146; P<br>
<br>
<br>
